The paper focuses on the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) in robots, specifically the NAO robot, which is commonly used in the field of robotics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of CNNs for object detection, which falls under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed design guidelines and the use of different CNN architectures also suggest that the paper may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the real-time processing of data, which is relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
